Dialog.text: Joan, please stop. You know I can't tell you-
Joan. Even with the reduced gravity, the moonstone that fell on him was... pretty big, Joan.
I can't tell you anything except we're going to do our best.
Tomorrow. Let us work on him.

Dialog.notes: [Chao Wei] Kinda rolling his eyes. Like, "quit bullshiting me"

Dialog.text: It might be more like getting sucked through a very tiny tiny straw.
Dialog.notes: [Chao Wei] Dryly joking, but considering the idea now.

Dialog.text: We'd need Riley's permission to run this.
Don't worry. We're safe up here.
The volunteer will come in first... right over there. Followed by the Typhon - which this week is a... Typhon Anthrophantasmus.
Huh. Two men enter, one man leaves.
Nah. The Typhon Gates keep everything locked down.
Oh, we don't let those into the crater. That would be a disaster.
Yep. It's like it's not even real.
I know. I'm just messing with you. Ready?
Well. It's a show. I'll give you that.
